Etymology[edit]

From adiuvō (“help, assist”) +‎ -tō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /adˈjuː.toː/, [ad̪ˈjuː.t̪oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /adˈju.to/, [ad̪ˈjuː.t̪ɔ]

Verb[edit]

adiūtō (present infinitive adiūtāre, perfect active adiūtāvī, supine adiūtātum); first conjugation

  1. I help, serve, assist.

Participle[edit]

adiūtō

  1. dative masculine singular of adiūtus
  2. dative neuter singular of adiūtus
  3. ablative masculine singular of adiūtus
  4. ablative neuter singular of adiūtus
